  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bca\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b85\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "American gift arrives in Colombo",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The P 627 Deep Sea Penetrating Vessel, officially handed over to the Sri Lankan Navy by the United States Coast Guard, has started its journey to Sri Lanka from the Port of Seattle, USA.",
        "On October 26, 2021, the ship was officially handed over to the Sri Lankan Navy by the United States Coast Guard.",
        "The ship, which started its journey to Colombo port on Saturday (03) after being modernized as per the operational requirements of the Sri Lankan Navy, will arrive in the first week of November, the Navy has announced.",
        "After the official handover, the vessel has been incorporated into the fleet of the Sri Lanka Navy under the number P627.",
        "The ship is said to be capable of conducting intrusion operations up to a range of at least 14,000 nautical miles."
      ],
